20:01.830 --> 20:03.786
and she mouthed something at me.

20:04.210 --> 20:08.499
I think it was, "Get the hell out."
So I left.

20:09.330 --> 20:12.618
-Did Chris see you?
-No, he wasn't there,

20:12.620 --> 20:15.828
but a friend was
at the head of the table.

20:15.830 --> 20:18.378
-You said, "a friend"?
-I saw someone.

20:18.380 --> 20:20.109
What did this person look like?

20:20.120 --> 20:24.955
I didn't see their face,
but tiny, really tiny.

20:25.460 --> 20:28.702
-White or black, Frank?
-I don't know, but...

20:28.710 --> 20:32.419
-What?
-The hair, it was red.

20:32.960 --> 20:36.418
If Frank saw them that day,
it wasn't Chris Crawford at the table.

20:36.420 --> 20:38.206
Maybe it was the suspect.

20:38.210 --> 20:41.668
And she wasn't saying, "Go away."
She was saying, "Help me."

20:47.790 --> 20:50.497
-It wasn't a friend.
-Frank.

20:50.790 --> 20:52.496
It wasn't a friend at all.

20:54.000 --> 20:55.456
It was him.

20:56.710 --> 20:58.575
He's the one who killed them.

21:01.420 --> 21:02.409
Frank.

21:04.580 --> 21:06.161
-Frank...
-No!No!No!

21:06.170 --> 21:07.910
-No!No!No!
-Frank, stop.

21:07.920 --> 21:10.741
-Frank, Frank.
-Let go!

21:10.750 --> 21:12.536
No, No!

21:12.540 --> 21:14.076
No!

21:14.080 --> 21:15.411
Frank!
-No!

21:15.420 --> 21:16.660
-Frank, calm down!
-No!

21:17.920 --> 21:19.535
-Frank! Come on!
-No,no!

21:21.250 --> 21:26.608
Both families had a dog
and both houses had a dog door.

21:28.460 --> 21:30.496
Fielding said that the person
he saw was small.

21:30.500 --> 21:33.162
Yeah, well, in order to get through
that door, you'd have to be 5'4", tops,

21:33.170 --> 21:34.285
and real thin.

21:34.290 --> 21:37.248
"When you have eliminated
the impossible, whatever remains,

21:37.250 --> 21:40.208
however improbable, must be the truth."

21:40.210 --> 21:42.246
Sherlock Holmes
was a fictional character.

21:42.250 --> 21:43.456
Whoever did this isn't.

21:43.460 --> 21:46.827
We can be pretty sure he's probably
found himself another family by now.

22:06.420 --> 22:08.570
-Let's just watch him sleep.
-No.

22:09.250 --> 22:11.571
We've got a long day ahead
of us tomorrow.

22:11.580 --> 22:14.378
-Can I kiss him?
-Both of you, out.

22:59.830 --> 23:03.288
Okay. No, I understand.
Yeah. I'd figured as much, thank you.

23:03.290 --> 23:05.576
He's been looking at those pictures
all morning.

23:05.580 --> 23:07.161
Well, I sure hope he sees a connection,

23:07.170 --> 23:10.788
because I've checked doctors, lawyers,
travel agents, tutors, contract workers...

23:10.790 --> 23:12.917
-I got nothing.
-Why target those families?

23:13.330 --> 23:14.786
Well, to know that,
we have to know how.

23:14.790 --> 23:17.702
All right, we know organised killers
are often skilled workers

23:17.710 --> 23:19.200
with above-average intelligence.

23:19.670 --> 23:22.662
A high birth status,

23:22.670 --> 23:25.707
and in most cases, male.

23:26.670 --> 23:29.070
In the workplace,
he's socially confident.

23:29.830 --> 23:33.459
And with women, sexually competent.

23:34.290 --> 23:37.032
Every offence is pre-planned.

23:38.750 --> 23:42.208
Targeting the victim is almost as
pleasurable as the actual kill.

23:42.210 --> 23:45.782
These guys, they're meticulous.
It's a compulsion.

23:45.790 --> 23:48.202
Everything has to have
its proper place.

23:48.210 --> 23:51.077
They do exhaustive amounts
of research on their victims.

23:51.750 --> 23:55.242
They watch their every move.
Every last detail is observed.

23:55.250 --> 23:59.493
Everything has to be written ever so
neatly in a book or possibly a journal.

23:59.500 --> 24:01.821
Like when the kids are coming home
from school,

24:01.830 --> 24:03.707
when Daddy will be home.

24:05.000 --> 24:09.039
Playtime, suppertime,
bath time, bedtime.

24:09.040 --> 24:11.577
Plan the work, work the plan.

24:11.580 --> 24:13.571
This is the way
that he maintains control.

24:14.000 --> 24:16.241
It's also how he personalises his target.

24:16.250 --> 24:19.117
So, nothing's left to chance,
and absolutely nothing

24:32.080 --> 24:34.207
is left out of place. Ever.

24:38.710 --> 24:41.167
So, he plans the work.

24:42.420 --> 24:45.162
And when he's good and ready,
he works that plan.

24:47.420 --> 24:49.376
He takes great pride in his job.

24:53.210 --> 24:55.826
I think the workplace
has to be the connection.

25:02.250 --> 25:05.822
This one is full of color and life.

25:06.170 --> 25:10.823
The one I found at Emily's house
has lines, dimensions, no color.

25:11.620 --> 25:14.418
I believe Emily was coerced
to paint this.

25:15.040 --> 25:18.749
It's a point of view.
It is his point of view.

25:19.540 --> 25:23.283
This is where the killer stood
and just watched the family.

25:29.750 --> 25:32.537
Each of the dead husbands
was missing his wedding ring.

25:32.540 --> 25:34.326
This is the UnSub's trophy.

25:34.710 --> 25:36.917
He targets a family
because he lost his own,

25:36.920 --> 25:38.956
and for a few days
he gets to play Daddy.

25:38.960 --> 25:41.246
And he can do whatever he wants
because no one's gonna come looking

25:41.250 --> 25:42.786
because they're supposed
to be on vacation.

25:42.790 --> 25:45.611
Let's get forensics to check the inside
of Chris Crawford's clothing.

25:45.620 --> 25:48.327
The suspect may've worn
the father's clothes, too.

25:48.330 --> 25:50.958
- Complete the fantasy.
-So why kill them?

25:51.420 --> 25:52.910
Because the fantasy can't last.

25:52.920 --> 25:56.708
Do we know anything that actually
helps us identify this bastard?

25:57.330 --> 25:58.820
Wait a minute.

25:59.380 --> 26:01.245
Chris Crawford worked for the IRS,

26:01.250 --> 26:05.493
and Reese Miller was a secretary
at the GAO.

26:06.170 --> 26:08.240
That makes them both
government employees.

26:08.250 --> 26:10.957
Let's check out
Chris Crawford and Reese Miller.

26:13.670 --> 26:16.161
He had his share of problems at home.
Who doesn't?

26:16.170 --> 26:18.741
But he didn't fix them
by killing his family.

26:18.750 --> 26:20.615
Were you aware he was in therapy?

26:20.620 --> 26:22.997
-He mentioned marriage counselling.
-He say who?

26:23.000 --> 26:26.322
Nope, and I didn't ask.
I don't like to pry.

26:26.330 --> 26:28.707
Well, that's surprising,
coming from an IRS agent.

26:30.960 --> 26:33.326
You mind if we go through
Chris' belongings,

26:33.330 --> 26:35.616
see if he had any connection to Miller?

26:36.000 --> 26:38.571
You're welcome to look through
anything you like.

26:42.710 --> 26:44.666
Family therapists.

26:44.670 --> 26:48.663
They often use children's paintings
to assess a family unit.

26:50.830 --> 26:52.707
We're all still in shock.

26:52.710 --> 26:55.372
Reese was a quiet woman.
She kept pretty much to herself,

26:55.380 --> 26:57.029
bell to bell, brought in her own lunch...

26:57.040 --> 26:58.325
-Mrs Raleigh...
-And she had two kids,

26:58.330 --> 26:59.911
but then you knew that.

26:59.920 --> 27:01.114
It's just so terrible.

27:01.120 --> 27:02.417
-I still can't believe it.
-Excuse me.

27:02.420 --> 27:05.241
And she was covering for one of
my women who is on maternity leave.

27:05.250 --> 27:08.162
She was always tired, you know.
But then, any woman married

27:08.170 --> 27:09.706
-to Eric Miller would be.
-Thanks.

27:09.710 --> 27:11.416
-He was a mean drunk.
-Mrs Raleigh?

27:11.420 --> 27:13.285
He hit her, you know.
She tried to cover it up.

27:13.290 --> 27:15.827
But concealer can only do
so much magic.

27:16.290 --> 27:18.030
-I should know.
-Mrs Raleigh...

27:18.040 --> 27:19.780
I'm sorry, I'm talking too much.

27:19.790 --> 27:22.702
Do you know if Mrs Miller was seeing
a marriage counsellor?

27:23.040 --> 27:26.328
-Reese kept pretty much to herself.
-You're not betraying any confidence.

27:26.330 --> 27:28.787
We need to know everything
about her life.

27:33.000 --> 27:34.240
Every Thursday I covered for her

27:34.250 --> 27:36.787
so she could take off early
to see a therapist.

27:37.500 --> 27:38.910
Thought it worked.

27:38.920 --> 27:42.242
She kicked the bastard out
and got remarried.

27:43.170 --> 27:44.819
Look what that got her.

27:47.500 --> 27:49.991
We've got to stop meeting
like this, Reid. People will talk.

27:50.000 --> 27:52.992
-But then, talk is cheap.
-Not when you're talking to a therapist.

27:53.250 --> 27:54.786
The Crawfords made
12 weekly payments

27:54.790 --> 27:58.749
to the Applewood Family Center.
What about the Millers?

27:59.460 --> 28:00.916
No, nothing here.

28:00.920 --> 28:02.990
How about pharmaceuticals?
No one gets therapy these days

28:03.000 --> 28:05.662
-without a healthy dose of medication.
-What're you implying, Reid?

28:06.000 --> 28:07.786
That everyone is medicated.

28:08.580 --> 28:10.912
-Did you just make a joke?
-No.

28:11.210 --> 28:14.418
-Statistics. They show that...
-Reid, next time, just say "yes", okay?

28:14.420 --> 28:17.662
Now, medication normally requires
a reimbursement from the HMO

28:17.670 --> 28:19.706
and since she works for
the government like you and I,

28:19.710 --> 28:21.951
we share the same
health care prowder.

28:22.790 --> 28:26.248
Are you hacking into
the government's HMO database?

28:26.250 --> 28:27.786
-Is that legal?
-Of course not.

28:27.790 --> 28:31.419
We'll both go to prison
and you'll be someone's bitch.

28:31.790 --> 28:33.576
-Rea|ly?
-Oh, right there.

28:33.580 --> 28:36.617
Good call, Reid.
Mrs Reese Miller, Diazepam.

28:37.000 --> 28:38.285
Who prescribed the meds?

28:38.290 --> 28:40.702
Dr R. Howard
at the Applewood Family Centre.

28:40.710 --> 28:43.281
Let's find out what he looks like.
Here we go.

28:47.080 --> 28:49.071
Dr Howard isn't a "he".

29:24.790 --> 29:27.611
Excellent, Lacy. Really wonderful.

29:27.620 --> 29:30.919
There's so much colour.
It's very lovely Indeed.

29:32.080 --> 29:33.820
Dr Rachel Howard,

29:34.080 --> 29:36.457
I'm Special Agent Aaron Hotchner
with the FBI.

29:36.460 --> 29:38.826
Come on, Lacy, come on.
Go with Mommy.

29:44.080 --> 29:45.456
Can I help you?

29:45.460 --> 29:48.031
I'm Agent Jason Gideon,
Behavioural Analysis.

29:48.040 --> 29:50.326
We both deal with the dysfunctional.

29:50.330 --> 29:54.209
Happily, in my line, the end results
aren't quite as unpleasant as yours.

29:54.620 --> 29:57.498
-Unless you're the Crawford family.
-Or the Millers. You knew them both.

29:57.500 --> 30:00.572
-Yes, I knew them.
-Ma'am,

30:00.580 --> 30:02.878
I think you should take a seat.

30:04.960 --> 30:06.029
Why?

30:07.500 --> 30:08.740
We're going
to have to check your alibi.

30:08.750 --> 30:11.537
Dig all you want. I have four teenagers.

30:11.540 --> 30:14.748
IfI had any time to myself,
it wouldn't be spent killing my clients.

30:14.750 --> 30:17.708
-You worked with both families?
-I assessed their cases.

30:17.710 --> 30:19.871
This office deals with
hundreds of families.

30:19.880 --> 30:22.576
Military, cops, lavwers,
congressmen, feds.

30:22.830 --> 30:25.116
I only met the Crawfords
and Reese Miller once.

30:25.120 --> 30:27.031
But you prescribed medication
for them?

30:27.040 --> 30:29.076
I'm the only medical doctor here.

30:29.330 --> 30:31.412
Who did you hand the cases over to?

30:31.420 --> 30:33.411
I'll have to check my files.

30:35.920 --> 30:37.535
You don't use a computer?

30:37.540 --> 30:39.781
Not all of us have embraced
the technical revolution.

30:39.790 --> 30:42.452
I keep everything filed,
it makes me feel more in control.

30:42.750 --> 30:44.877
And please, do not read into that.

30:48.250 --> 30:51.879
The Crawfords.
Karl Arnold dealt with their case.

30:51.880 --> 30:53.950
-What about the Millers?
-We'd like to see him now.

30:53.960 --> 30:56.747
We can't. He works a four-forty.
Four ten-hour days.

30:56.750 --> 30:58.741
He's off today,
but he'll be in first thing tomorrow.

30:58.750 --> 31:00.615
Do you have his home address?

31:02.580 --> 31:04.286
I'll get a team out to his house.

31:04.290 --> 31:06.417
In the meantime,
I'd like to see his office.

31:08.750 --> 31:10.706
The suspect's cell is going straight
to voice mail.

31:10.710 --> 31:12.075
Karl's a good man.

31:12.750 --> 31:15.992
That's what everybody says
until they find a body in the basement.

31:16.000 --> 31:17.615
-It's locked.
-I'll get security.

31:18.040 --> 31:19.780
No, we don't have time for that.

31:27.210 --> 31:30.247
-Someone will have to pay for that.
-Karl Arnold will.

31:33.210 --> 31:34.575
Gideon?

31:39.790 --> 31:41.109
Where is he now?

31:42.040 --> 31:44.281
-I can't believe Karl...
-Where is he?

31:45.170 --> 31:46.455
I don't know.

31:46.460 --> 31:49.497
If he's not at home
maybe he's gone to see his family.

31:49.960 --> 31:51.109
He's married?

31:51.120 --> 31:53.076
With two children. Karl Jr, and Sarah.

31:53.080 --> 31:55.412
How long ago
did the marriage collapse?

31:57.710 --> 32:01.202
About five years ago.
It wasn't a good time for Karl.

32:02.170 --> 32:03.990
He took some time off work.

32:04.000 --> 32:07.572
He couldn't concentrate,
he started drinking.

32:07.580 --> 32:08.911
-Yeah.
-I can't believe...

32:08.920 --> 32:10.660
What do you got?

32:10.670 --> 32:12.285
I would've seen...

32:13.920 --> 32:15.660
Oh, my God, I feel sick.

32:15.670 --> 32:17.570
Where does Karl's family live?

32:18.000 --> 32:19.740
She took the kids and moved to Idaho.

32:19.750 --> 32:21.615
They just raided Karl's home.

32:22.710 --> 32:24.416
He's not there.

32:43.880 --> 32:45.950
Cut it out, now. Both of you.

32:45.960 --> 32:48.372
Sarah, Karl Jr, go do your homework!

32:50.080 --> 32:52.071
Don't do that! That's not funny!

32:52.420 --> 32:53.489
Hello?

32:53.500 --> 32:56.287
VVhat

32:56.290 --> 32:58.326
Fay Arnold,
this is Federal Agent Aaron Hotchner.

32:58.330 --> 32:59.911
I'd like to know where
your ex-husband is.

32:59.920 --> 33:02.377
As long as he's nowhere near me,
I don't give a damn.

33:02.750 --> 33:04.820
We really need to find him.
When was the last time you saw him?

33:04.830 --> 33:07.822
I haven't seen him in over two years.

33:07.830 --> 33:09.457
He's a scary guy.

33:10.170 --> 33:12.786
But he did call me about an hour ago.

33:12.790 --> 33:14.826
I wish he would just go to hell
and stay there.

33:14.830 --> 33:15.956
What did he say?

33:15.960 --> 33:19.168
He just babbled on about
how precious family is.

33:19.790 --> 33:22.247
-Did he say where he was?
-No,no.

33:22.250 --> 33:24.411
He just wanted to talk to the kids.

33:24.710 --> 33:28.498
He said he'd just met a little girl
that reminded him of my Sarah.

33:28.500 --> 33:30.786
Did he seem upset Confused?

33:30.790 --> 33:35.113
He seemed like he always is.
Angry, controlling, manic.

33:35.460 --> 33:37.246
Do you have any idea
where he might be?

33:37.250 --> 33:38.410
No.

33:38.420 --> 33:43.323
But I did hear kids in the background,
and then someone started to cry.

33:43.330 --> 33:45.491
-That's when he hung up.
-Thank you.

33:49.540 --> 33:52.498
Arnold just called her.
She heard kids in the background.

33:52.500 --> 33:54.991
He's already in another family's house.

34:02.170 --> 34:03.819
Hotch, there's gotta be
hundreds of families here.

34:03.830 --> 34:06.492
Then we'll send an agent to
every last one of them if we have to.

34:06.500 --> 34:09.663
Karl Arnold, he has a boy and a girl,
just like the Millers and the Crawfords.

34:10.040 --> 34:12.452
-Target family will be the same.
-How could I have not seen it?

34:12.460 --> 34:13.745
Well, because he's that good.

34:13.750 --> 34:15.536
If he wasn't,
we would've caught him sooner.

34:15.540 --> 34:16.700
Does he have a journal?

34:16.710 --> 34:18.701
He writes everything down,
takes it everywhere.

34:18.710 --> 34:20.029
It's likely he also collects trophies.

34:20.040 --> 34:22.668
If they're not in his house,
they're right here, hidden in this room.

34:22.670 --> 34:25.207
From the families he killed.

34:25.210 --> 34:26.825
If he doesn't confess,
we'll need them as evidence.

34:26.830 --> 34:28.991
Here's one, the Harrises.
One boy, one girl.

34:29.000 --> 34:30.456
I've got a few.

34:30.750 --> 34:33.878
-The Boyds and the Dunkens.
-Wait. The Dunkens.

34:33.880 --> 34:36.531
That's not one of his cases,
that's mine.

34:36.540 --> 34:38.167
They have a baby boy

34:38.170 --> 34:41.708
and a slightly introverted
eight-year-old named Jackie.

34:41.710 --> 34:43.371
Jackie.

34:45.580 --> 34:48.458
-Jackie's work?
-He took it from my office.

34:48.460 --> 34:50.576
-Were they planning a trip?
-To the Adirondacks.

34:50.580 --> 34:53.208
-Let's go. Hotch, tear up the room.
-Here, take this.

34:53.830 --> 34:54.876
I'll call you some backup.

35:02.330 --> 35:06.164
We've got three adults, two children,
sitting at the dining room table.

35:19.960 --> 35:22.246
[-FBI! FBI!
-He 5 got my baby!

35:22.670 --> 35:24.570
-Ma'am, is he alone?
-Yes, he is!

35:24.580 --> 35:26.957
Where's the basement?
-Under the stairs!

35:26.960 --> 35:28.245
Son of a bitch.

35:28.250 --> 35:30.707
Get them out of here!
Get them out of here!

35:33.920 --> 35:35.160
Gideon! Gideon!

35:52.790 --> 35:53.779
Karl?

35:56.380 --> 35:58.109
Karl, it's the FBI.

36:08.170 --> 36:09.159
Karl...

36:09.920 --> 36:10.989
Shh.

36:13.790 --> 36:15.781
Why don't you give me the baby?

36:21.380 --> 36:22.369
Karl.

36:25.830 --> 36:27.457
Karl, I want you to look at me.

36:28.330 --> 36:33.495
I'm gonna put my gun away.
And I want you to hand me that baby.

36:51.500 --> 36:52.819
Hand me the baby.

36:56.420 --> 36:57.409
Knife!

37:05.540 --> 37:07.917
You move, I will break your neck.

37:11.920 --> 37:13.114
Okay.

37:20.210 --> 37:21.279
Hello.

37:23.420 --> 37:24.876
Let's go.

37:28.830 --> 37:31.071
Keep it moving.

37:37.210 --> 37:39.166
-Did he say anything?
-No.

37:40.420 --> 37:42.786
Can we tie him forensically
to the other crimes?

37:42.790 --> 37:46.248
Negative on foreign DNA.
He must've washed Crawford's clothes.

37:46.250 --> 37:48.241
Then we'll need a confession.

37:48.250 --> 37:50.457
-Can you get one

37:50.460 --> 37:52.701
-Yeah.
-Then, maybe.

37:54.960 --> 37:58.703
Emily Crawford was a very talented
and gifted girl.

37:59.420 --> 38:02.662
Her brother Sam,
a bright, energetic child.

38:04.250 --> 38:07.959
You watched them from the yard
for days, maybe even weeks.

38:08.750 --> 38:11.958
You learned everything about them.
You studied their every move

38:11.960 --> 38:13.916
and then you wrote it all down.

38:14.330 --> 38:16.207
May I have a glass of water?

38:16.580 --> 38:19.378
-Something wrong?
-No, I'm just thirsty.

38:20.960 --> 38:22.496
Water, please.

38:24.120 --> 38:26.702
Could you remove my shackles?
I'm clearly no threat to you.

38:27.040 --> 38:28.780
They stay on.

38:33.290 --> 38:36.498
_ You chose families that
reminded you of the one you lost.

38:36.960 --> 38:38.825
You stalked them, you bound them,

38:38.830 --> 38:41.242
you terrorised them,
and then you killed them.

38:41.500 --> 38:42.615
One by one.

38:44.460 --> 38:46.280
We have your journals, Karl.

38:48.120 --> 38:50.577
It's my job,

38:51.500 --> 38:53.957
to write everything down,
to get to know them.

38:53.960 --> 38:57.111
I can't help them solve their problems
without knowing background.

38:57.120 --> 38:59.668
I make home visits.

39:00.080 --> 39:03.117
Sometimes without their knowledge,
because people lie.

39:03.120 --> 39:05.452
You, of all people, should know that.

39:12.920 --> 39:17.789
Eric Miller was
an awful husband and father.

39:18.120 --> 39:21.374
Allison Crawford haemorrhaged money
her husband didn't have.

39:21.380 --> 39:23.245
That can strain any marriage.

39:29.920 --> 39:32.320
On the surface,
this looks like "any family, USA".

39:32.330 --> 39:34.537
Two-parent household,
two kids, a boy and a girl.

39:34.830 --> 39:36.036
But if you look a little closer,

39:36.040 --> 39:38.702
you'll see their body language
tells a different story.

39:38.710 --> 39:41.611
The woman and children
are distant from the man.

39:41.620 --> 39:44.418
Their smiles are stiff,
their eyes are frightened.

39:44.670 --> 39:48.037
Every hair is in place,
wearing their Sunday best.

39:48.540 --> 39:51.498
Their own private hell
being memorialised on film.

39:58.960 --> 40:00.416
Are you okay?

40:03.210 --> 40:04.450
It isn't right.

40:06.380 --> 40:07.665
What isn't?

40:08.170 --> 40:11.116
You've got the pictures mixed up!

40:11.670 --> 40:15.538
The one in the middle,
that is Sam Crawford's.

40:16.620 --> 40:20.112
It should be Ty Miller's!

40:21.460 --> 40:25.749
You need to swap them.
You need to make it right.

40:26.790 --> 40:27.950
This one here?

40:29.290 --> 40:32.282
What the hell
have I been trying to tell you?

40:32.710 --> 40:35.247
You're right. They're switched.

40:36.040 --> 40:38.998
That is Sam Crawford's foot
with the Miller family.

40:39.000 --> 40:41.161
But how did you know that, Karl?

40:59.250 --> 41:02.413
And I watched them
for a number of days.

41:03.420 --> 41:05.285
Always at night.

41:05.960 --> 41:09.999
Saw how they lived, how they loved.

41:10.710 --> 41:16.068
I would keep them apart until
the last night, until the last supper.

41:17.380 --> 41:19.746
Then I would bring them, one by one,

41:21.790 --> 41:23.496
down to the basement.

41:25.170 --> 41:29.789
The youngest first, the father last.

41:29.790 --> 41:31.109
Why, Karl?

41:34.420 --> 41:38.413
So he could see
what happens to families

41:38.960 --> 41:42.999
when the head of household
isn't strong.

41:47.880 --> 41:52.032
Wives wither, children perish.

41:57.460 --> 42:00.668
But me, I'm an excellent father.
